events.description:
Free Admission!

A concert featuring compositions by Herb Alpert Award recipient and flutist Nicole Mitchell. Mitchell is joined by three-time Grammy Award-winner Billy Childs on piano, vocal legend Dwight Trible, and internationally renowned bass player Mark Dresser.

Mitchell is an award-winning creative flutist, composer, bandleader, educator and transdisciplinary conceptualist. Mitchell believes in the transformational power of music, and she seeks to build alternative worlds that bridge the familiar with the unknown. Her mission as a flutist has been to raise respect for the instrument by developing a new improvisational language that incorporates her voice with the flute. The founder of Black Earth Ensemble, Mitchell composes for contemporary ensembles of varied instrumentation and size, while incorporating improvisation and a wide aesthetic expression. She is a Professor of Music at University of California, Irvine.

Parking for Jan Popper Theater is in Parking Structure 2. Find maps and parking rates here.

events.description:
The aerospace industry is in a period of transformation from a smaller number of typically large “traditional” aerospace & defense companies (i.e. Boeing, Northrop Grumman) to include a proliferation of small and not so small commercial “NewSpace” companies (or “Space 2.0” or private spaceflight”, i.e. Virgin Orbit, Millennium, Facebook etc). 

This panel of Industry experts explores how companies adapt and innovate product development in the NewSpace economy.
In addition to technology and product development, the panel will include coverage of business models and financing.

Confirmed Speakers:
James Myers ('94) – Sector VP, Northrop Grumman Corp.
Richard Milford ('04) – Sr. Director System Engineering, Virgin Orbit
Jason Kim ('09) – VP Strategic Planning, Millennium
Jim Adams ('05) – Partner, PwC Strategy
Mario Furtado ('12) – Sr. Principal Systems Engineer, Raytheon

Moderated by: 
Amir Blachman ('03) – VP Strategic Development, Axiom Space

events.description:
FREE FLU SHOTS from the UCLA Arthur Ashe Student Health & Wellness Center at the ANDERSON SCHOOL COURTYARD!

What causes chills, muscle aches, a fever, and can last 4-6 weeks? If you guessed “the flu,” you're absolutely correct! And those are just some of the symptoms that might keep you out of class and away from those study sessions. Here’s a pro tip: Avoid the flu all together with a flu shot from the Ashe Center! Getting a flu shot is a fast, easy way to protect yourself and to ensure that you don’t miss class and fall behind academically.

Join us for our Annual Flu Fair events on campus to receive your free flu shot:

Visit our Ashe Center website Event Calendar for additional pop up flu fair dates.

*NEXT MONDAY, NOVEMBER 13, FLU FAIR WILL BE HELD AT THE LAW SCHOOL COURTYARD.

If you can’t make it to our Flu Fairs, you can schedule an appointment for a free flu shot online, by phone or in person at The Ashe Center.

For additional Flu Fair dates, or to make a flu shot appointment, visit: http://www.studenthealth.ucla.edu/
